title: Drawing, "End Table", September 1, 1933
medium: Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite
markings: Stamp in black ink, lower right: DONALD DESKEY/145 WEST 57TH STREET/NEW YORK CITY [stamped over identical stamp in red ink]
inscribed: Inscribed in graphite at lower left: BL.-S.-W. Inscribed in graphite at lower left: 6 Inscribed in red color pencil at lower right: P Inscribed dimensions
description: Perspective, plan, and elevation for small end table, probably wood and/or lacquer. Rectangular surface on top extends over left side; two shelves below. Table supported by base of darker wood. Asymmetrical overall shape and placement of shelves.

tombstone.epitaph:
Drawing, "End Table", September 1, 1933.
September 1, 1933. Graphite on tracing paper, ruled border in graphite. Gift of Donald Deskey. 1988-101-865.
